{"id":1354360936,"question_id":12,"lang":"c","lang_name":"C","time":"5 months, 2 weeks","timestamp":1723558890,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1354360936/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Integer to Roman","memory":"9.3 MB","code":"#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\n#include <string.h>\n\nchar* intToRoman(int num) {\n    // Define arrays for Roman numeral values and their corresponding symbols\n    int values[] = {1000, 900, 500, 400, 100, 90, 50, 40, 10, 9, 5, 4, 1};\n    char* symbols[] = {\"M\", \"CM\", \"D\", \"CD\", \"C\", \"XC\", \"L\", \"XL\", \"X\", \"IX\", \"V\", \"IV\", \"I\"};\n    \n    // Allocate a buffer to store the result. 20 characters should be enough for any valid input.\n    char* result = (char*)malloc(20 * sizeof(char));\n    result[0] = '\\0'; // Initialize the result string\n\n    // Loop through each value-symbol pair\n    for (int i = 0; i < 13; i++) {\n        // While the number is greater than or equal to the current value\n        while (num >= values[i]) {\n            // Subtract the value from the number\n            num -= values[i];\n            // Append the corresponding symbol to the result string\n            strcat(result, symbols[i]);\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Return the constructed Roman numeral string\n    return result;\n}\n\n\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"integer-to-roman","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
